<inglise> (5) Article 30(3) of Regulation (EC) No 1260/1999 provides that rules on eligible expenditure should be the relevant national rules unless the Commission deems it necessary to adopt rules at Community level; for certain types of operation the Commission considers it necessary in order to guarantee the uniform and equitable implementation of the Structural Funds across the Community to adopt a common set of rules on eligible expenditure. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1260/1999 artikli 30 l&otilde;ikes 3 on s&auml;testatud, et abik&otilde;lblike kulutuste suhtes kohaldatakse asjakohaseid siseriiklikke eeskirju, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui komisjon peab vajalikuks vastu v&otilde;tta eeskirjad &uuml;henduse tasandil; teatavate meetmete puhul peab komisjon vajalikuks vastu v&otilde;tta abik&otilde;lblikke kulutusi k&auml;sitlevad &uuml;hiseeskirjad, et tagada struktuurifondide &uuml;htne ja &otilde;iglane rakendamine &uuml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise> The adoption of a rule relating to a particular type of operation does not prejudge under which of the abovementioned Funds such operation may be co-financed. </inglise>
