<inglise> Rule No 2: accounting treatment of receipts </inglise>
<eesti> Eeskiri 2: laekumiste k&auml;sitlemine raamatupidamises </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> "Receipts" for the purposes of this rule covers revenue received by an operation during the period of its co-financing or during such longer period up to the closure of the assistance as may be fixed by the Member State, from sales, rentals, services, enrolment/fees or other equivalent receipts with the exception of: </inglise>
<eesti> Laekumised k&auml;esoleva eeskirja t&auml;henduses h&otilde;lmavad tulu, mis saadakse meetme kaasfinantseerimisperioodil v&otilde;i, kui liikmesriik selle kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rab, pikema ajavahemiku jooksul kuni abi l&otilde;petamiseni, m&uuml;&uuml;gist, rentimisest, teenustest, liitumistasudest v&otilde;i muudest samav&auml;&auml;rsetest laekumistest, v&auml;lja arvatud: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) receipts generated throughout the economic lifetime of the co-financed investments and subject to the specific provisions of Article 29(4) of the General Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> a) laekumised, mis saadakse kaasfinantseeritavate investeeringute majandusliku eluea jooksul ning mille suhtes kohaldatakse &uuml;ldm&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 29 l&otilde;ike 4 eris&auml;tteid; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) receipts generated within the framework of financial engineering measures referred to in Rules 8, 9 and 10; </inglise>
<eesti> b) laekumised eeskirjades 8, 9 ja 10 osutatud finantskorraldusmeetmete raames; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) contributions from the private sector to the co-financing of operations, which appear alongside public contributions in the financing tables of the relevant assistance. </inglise>
<eesti> c) erasektorist meetmete kaasfinantseerimiseks antavad toetused, mis kirjendatakse koos avalike toetustega asjaomase abivormi rahastamistabelitesse. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Receipts under point 1 represent income which reduces the amount of co-financing under the Structural Funds that is required for the operation in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Punktile 1 vastavaid laekumisi k&auml;sitatakse tuluna, mis v&auml;hendab k&otilde;nealuse meetme puhul n&otilde;utavat struktuurifondide kaasfinantseerimismahtu. </eesti>
<inglise> Before the Structural Funds' participation is calculated and no later than at the time of the closure of the assistance, they are deducted from the operation's eligible expenditure in their entirety or pro rata, depending on whether they were generated entirely or only in part by the co-financed operation. </inglise>
<eesti> Need lahutatakse enne struktuurifondide osaluse arvutamist v&otilde;i hiljemalt abi l&otilde;petamisel meetme abik&otilde;lblikest kulutustest kas t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i proportsionaalselt, olenevalt sellest, kas need p&auml;rinevad t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i osaliselt kaasfinantseeritud meetmest. </eesti>
<inglise> Rule No 3: financial and other charges and legal expenses </inglise>
<eesti> Eeskiri 3: finantseerimis- ja muud kulud ning kohtukulud </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> FINANCIAL CHARGES </inglise>
<eesti> FINANTSEERIMISKULUD </eesti>
<inglise> Debit interest (other than expenditure on interest subsidies to reduce the cost of borrowing for businesses under an approved State aid scheme), charges for financial transactions, foreign exchange commissions and losses, and other purely financial expenses are not eligible for co-financing by the Structural Funds. </inglise>
<eesti> V&otilde;laintressid (v&auml;lja arvatud kulud intressitoetustele, mille eesm&auml;rk on v&auml;hendada ettev&otilde;tete laenukulusid heakskiidetud riigiabi programmi alusel), finantstehingute kulud, valuutavahetustasud ja valuutakahjum ning muud &uuml;ksnes finantseerimisega seotud kulutused ei ole struktuurifondide kaasfinantseerimiseks k&otilde;lblikud. </eesti>
<inglise> However, in the sole case of global grants, debit interest charges paid by the designated intermediary prior to payment of the final balance of the assistance are eligible, after deduction of credit interest on advances. </inglise>
<eesti> Ainult &uuml;ldiste toetuste puhul k&auml;sitatakse m&auml;&auml;ratud vahendaja poolt enne abi l&otilde;ppmakse tegemist makstavaid v&otilde;laintresse abik&otilde;lblikuna p&auml;rast seda, kui ettemaksetelt n&otilde;utav krediidiintress on tasutud. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> BANK CHARGES ON ACCOUNTS </inglise>
<eesti> PANGAKONTO HOOLDUSTASUD </eesti>
<inglise> Where co-financing by the Structural Funds requires the opening of a separate account or accounts for implementing an operation, the bank charges for opening and administering the accounts, are eligible. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui struktuurifondide kaasfinantseerimine eeldab meetme rakendamiseks eraldi pangakonto v&otilde;i -kontode avamist, k&auml;sitatakse pangakontode avamise ja haldamisega seoses pangale makstavaid tasusid abik&otilde;lblikena. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> LEGAL FEES FOR ADVICE, NOTARY FEES, THE COSTS OF TECHNICAL OR FINANCIAL EXPERTISE, AND ACCOUNTANCY OR AUDIT COSTS </inglise>
<eesti> JURIIDILISE N&Otilde;USTAMISE TASUD, NOTARITASUD, TEHNILISE V&Otilde;I FINANTSEKSPERTIISI KULUD NING RAAMATUPIDAMIS- V&Otilde;I AUDITEERIMISKULUD </eesti>
<inglise> These costs are eligible if they are directly linked to the operation and are necessary for its preparation or implementation or, in the case of accounting or audit costs, if they relate to requirements by the managing authority. </inglise>
<eesti> Need kulud on abik&otilde;lblikud, kui need on otseselt seotud meetmega ning vajalikud selle ettevalmistamiseks v&otilde;i rakendamiseks v&otilde;i, raamatupidamis- v&otilde;i auditeerimiskulude puhul, kui need on seotud korraldusasutuse n&otilde;uetega. </eesti>
